Europe<-Europe%>%mutate(dollars_per_day=gdp/population/365)


#Lets see differences between past years and present ones

gapminder%>%mutate(dollars_per_day=gdp/population/365)%>%filter(continent=="Europe" & year==present_year & !is.na(gdp))%>%
  ggplot(aes(dollars_per_day))+
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1,colour="black")+
  scale_x_continuous(trans="log2")

p<-gapminder%>%
  filter(year==past_year & !is.na(gdp))%>%
  mutate(region=reorder(region,dollars_per_day,median))%>%
  ggplot(aes(region,dollars_per_day,fill=continent))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  geom_jitter()+
  scale_y_continuous(trans="log2")+
  xlab("Region")+
  ylab("Dollars per Day")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(hjust=1,angle=45))+
  ggtitle("Dollars per Day in 1970")
p

s<-gapminder%>%
  filter(year==present_year & !is.na(gdp))%>%
  mutate(region=reorder(region,dollars_per_day,median))%>%
  ggplot(aes(region,dollars_per_day,fill=continent))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  geom_jitter()+
  scale_y_continuous(trans="log2")+
  xlab("Region")+
  ylab("Dollars per Day")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(hjust=1,angle=45))+
  ggtitle("Dollars per Day in 2010")
s

# See the Differences Between 1970's dollars per day and 2010's.
library(gridExtra)

grid.arrange(p,s)
